  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Caption</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Slot an <code>&lt;address&gt;</code> (or any content) as a caption overlay at the bottom of the map. This content is also the no-JS fallback.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Caption slot">{{ captionCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>No-JS Fallback</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Before the component upgrades, the slotted content is visible as a styled card. Include a link to OpenStreetMap so users can still find the location.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Progressive enhancement">{{ fallbackCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Data Binding</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Coordinates can come from 6 sources, checked in priority order. The first match wins:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Explicit <code>lat</code>/<code>lng</code> attributes</strong> &mdash; highest priority</li>
        <li><strong><code>src</code> &rarr; <code>&lt;address data-lat data-lng&gt;</code></strong> &mdash; reference an external address element by ID</li>
        <li><strong><code>src</code> &rarr; <code>&lt;script type="application/ld+json"&gt;</code></strong> &mdash; reference a JSON-LD script by ID</li>
        <li><strong>Slotted <code>&lt;address data-lat data-lng&gt;</code></strong> &mdash; address inside the component</li>
        <li><strong><code>place</code> attribute</strong> &mdash; scans all JSON-LD scripts for a matching <code>name</code></li>
        <li><strong><code>&lt;meta name="geo.position"&gt;</code></strong> &mdash; page-level fallback</li>
      </ol>
    </layout-text>

    <h3><code>src</code> &rarr; address element</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Point <code>src</code> to the ID of an <code>&lt;address&gt;</code> element with <code>data-lat</code> and <code>data-lng</code> attributes. The address stays visible as semantic content while the map reads its coordinates.</p>
    </layout-text>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="src → address">{{ srcAddressCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3><code>src</code> &rarr; JSON-LD script</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Point <code>src</code> to the ID of a <code>&lt;script type="application/ld+json"&gt;</code> element. The component reads <code>geo.latitude</code> and <code>geo.longitude</code> from the parsed JSON.</p>
    </layout-text>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="src → JSON-LD">{{ srcJsonLdCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Slotted <code>&lt;address&gt;</code> with coordinates</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Slot an <code>&lt;address&gt;</code> with <code>data-lat</code> and <code>data-lng</code> directly inside the component. The address appears as a caption and also provides the coordinates.</p>
    </layout-text>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Slotted address">{{ slottedAddressCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3><code>place</code> attribute</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Set <code>place</code> to a name that matches the <code>name</code> field in a JSON-LD <code>Place</code> script anywhere on the page. Useful when structured data already exists for SEO.</p>
    </layout-text>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="place attribute">{{ placeCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3><code>&lt;meta&gt;</code> fallback</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>As a last resort, the component checks for a <code>&lt;meta name="geo.position"&gt;</code> tag in the document. The content format is <code>"lat;lng"</code>.</p>
    </layout-text>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Meta fallback">{{ metaCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

