  <section>
    <h2>Interactive Mode</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>By default, hovering over the map reveals a "Click to interact" button. Clicking activates pan and zoom &mdash; no external libraries loaded. The interactive layer is lazy-loaded on first activation.</p>
      <p>Use <code>interactive="eager"</code> to activate immediately, <code>interactive="none"</code> to hide the button, or <code>static-only</code> to fully prevent interaction.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <div class="example">
      <layout-stack data-layout-gap="m">
        <div>
          <strong>Click to activate (default)</strong>
          <geo-map lat="40.7484" lng="-73.9857" zoom="15" style="--geo-map-height: 250px;">
            <address>Hover, then click to interact. Drag to pan, scroll to zoom, Escape to exit.</address>
          </geo-map>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Static only</strong>
          <geo-map lat="35.6762" lng="139.6503" zoom="13" static-only provider="carto-light" style="--geo-map-height: 200px;">
            <address>Tokyo &mdash; no interaction</address>
          </geo-map>
        </div>
      </layout-stack>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Interactive variants">{{ interactiveCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

